description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/25478/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for trinexapac-ethyl in the Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;Trinexapac-ethyl is an organic substance with the CAS no.: 095266-40-3. It is called 'ethyl 4-[cyclopropyl(hydroxy)methylene]-3,5-dioxocyclohexanecarboxylate' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C13H16O5. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure as a white powder. It is modelled as a pure substance. Trinexapac-ethyl is a plant growth regulator for grain, grass and rape. There are no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce trinexapac-ethyl within the geography of GLO.

This activity ends with the supply of trinexapac-ethyl  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.
